{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PSBCH scrambling for remaining bits in Sidelink\n\n### Summary\nThe PSBCH scrambling function `sl_psbch_scrambling()` in the NR UE transport module had two issues that caused incorrect scrambling of the encoded PSBCH payload:\n\n1. Operator precedence error in bit manipulation expression that caused incorrect extraction of scrambling bits for remaining bits (<32 bits)\n2. Incorrect scrambling sequence continuity - the remaining bits were being scrambled with bits from the previous scrambling word instead of generating a new word\n\nThese issues caused incorrect PSBCH transmission that failed gNB decoding during sidelink operations. The problem was particularly noticeable when the encoded PSBCH length was not a multiple of 32 bits (which occurs with normal cyclic prefix).\n\nThe fix ensures proper bit-level scrambling according to 3GPP TS 38.211 specifications by:\n1. Correcting operator precedence in bit extraction\n2. Generating a new scrambling word for remaining bits to maintain sequence continuity\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_UE_TRANSPORT/nr_psbch_tx.c`: Fixed operator precedence in bit manipulation and added proper scrambling word generation for remaining bits in `sl_psbch_scrambling()`\n"
}